==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Longtail
<hw>Long"tail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An animal,
particularly a log, having an uncut tail. Cf. <er>Curtail</er>.
<er>Dog</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A <xex>longtail</xex> was a gentleman's dog, or the dog
of one qualified to bunt, other dogs being required to have their tails
cut.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cut and longtail</b></col>, <cd>all, gentlefolks and
others, as they might come.</cd> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>long-term</ent>⟦br⟧
